---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Placeholder from '../components/Placeholder.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Philosophy"
  description="Unapologetically choosing yourself. The Kamala manifesto and the way we hold the weekend."
>
  <section class="pt-12 lg:pt-20 pb-16 lg:pb-24">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 items-center">
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 space-y-8">
        <p class="eyebrow">The Kamala philosophy</p>
        <h1 class="font-light">Unapologetically <em class="text-gold-600">choosing yourself.</em></h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
          Taking the time, and the courage, to rise through the murky waters. Letting the world bask in awe at the very best version of you &mdash; not because you performed it, but because you finally let it through.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-5">
        <Placeholder ratio="4/5" label="Hands · still life" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 border-t border-sand/60">
    <figure class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center space-y-8">
      <p class="eyebrow">The manifesto</p>
      <blockquote class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-display italic text-ink leading-snug">
        We navigate beautifully humbling hurdles. We move through ebbs and flows we didn't choose. The work is to reflect, to appreciate, to celebrate the journey as it actually is &mdash; not as we wish it had been.
      </blockquote>
      <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl font-display italic text-gold-700">
        And in that acceptance, everything changes.
      </p>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section id="trust" class="py-16 lg:py-24 border-t border-sand/60 scroll-mt-24">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="lg:col-span-4">
        <p class="eyebrow">One</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4">Trust the process</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 space-y-6 text-ink-soft text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>Most of the time, the process doesn't look like progress.</p>
        <p>
          It looks like sitting with something you'd rather not sit with. It looks like a journal entry that goes nowhere. It looks like crying in a room full of strangers and not knowing why.
        </p>
        <p>
          Trusting the process means showing up to the next thing on the schedule even when you can't see the point yet. It means letting the weekend do what weekends like this do. It means not needing the answer before the question has finished forming.
        </p>
        <p class="font-display italic text-2xl text-ink leading-snug pt-2">
          You don't have to believe in any of it. You just have to keep showing up.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="comfortable" class="py-16 lg:py-24 border-t border-sand/60 scroll-mt-24">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="lg:col-span-4">
        <p class="eyebrow">Two</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4">Get comfortable with being uncomfortable</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 space-y-6 text-ink-soft text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p class="font-display italic text-2xl text-ink">Discomfort is information.</p>
        <p>
          The breath that catches in your chest during somatic work. The tightness in your jaw during the gong. The thing you almost said at dinner and didn't. These aren't problems to fix &mdash; they're places the body has been holding something on your behalf, sometimes for years.
        </p>
        <p>
          We're not interested in pushing past discomfort. We're interested in sitting near it. Long enough that it can speak. Long enough that something in you can answer back.
        </p>
        <p>
          The weekend is held so that you can do this safely. With practitioners who know what they're doing. In a room where nobody is watching, and nobody is asking you to be okay.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="work" class="py-16 lg:py-24 border-t border-sand/60 scroll-mt-24">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="lg:col-span-4">
        <p class="eyebrow">Three</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4">Do the work</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 space-y-6 text-ink-soft text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>There's no version of this where the work gets done for you.</p>
        <p>
          We can hold the cacao, light the candles, set the room. We can bring you food that nourishes you and music that moves you. We can put a sound healer at the edge of the pool while you float.
        </p>
        <p class="font-display italic text-2xl text-ink">But the work &mdash; the actual rising &mdash; is yours.</p>
        <p>
          It's the choice to put your phone away. To say the thing you came here to say. To let the breath go where it wants to go. To stop performing, even just for the weekend, even just for an hour.
        </p>
        <div class="pt-4 space-y-1 font-display italic text-2xl text-ink">
          <p>This is where we grow.</p>
          <p>This is where we rise.</p>
          <p>This is where we glow.</p>
          <p class="text-gold-700 pt-2">This is Kamala.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 border-t border-sand/60">
    <div class="rounded-(--radius-card) bg-cream-deep border border-sand/70 px-8 py-14 lg:px-16 lg:py-20 text-center space-y-6">
      <p class="eyebrow">Come and meet it</p>
      <h2 class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">If something in this is calling you, come.</h2>
      <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto">
        We run a small number of retreats each year. Each one is held in a private estate, capped at a small group, with practitioners chosen for how they hold space together.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 pt-4">
        <a href="/retreats" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3.5 rounded-(--radius-pill) bg-ink text-cream text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] hover:bg-gold-700 transition-colors">See upcoming retreats</a>
        <a href="/faq" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3.5 rounded-(--radius-pill) border border-ink/15 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] hover:border-ink/40 transition-colors">Read the FAQ</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
